Make marinade: stir together juice concentrate, oil, vinegar, soy sauce, rosemary, cinnamon, cloves, and pepper in medium bowl. Pour some marinade into 13-inch by 9-inch glass baking dish. Add first ham steak, more marinade, second ham steak, and rest of marinade. Cover dish and refrigerate at least 1 hour. Spray cold grill and utensils well with cooking spray. Position grill 3 to 4 inches from heat. Heat grill according to manufacturer's suggestion. Remove ham steaks from marinade and place on grate. Grill 3 to 5 minutes per side, turning once. Garnish with rosemary sprigs.